@ThinkingandTinkering Oh, that's not what I meant.. the clutches, everything else would be the same (thinking of the smaller model) but the larger planet gears wouldn't actually fit on the frame, so have one in mesh with the small planet gear, and then the next gear/clutch in line would just sit 'above' the last one, overlapped, still in mesh with the planet gear. Just a way to get the ratio down without growing the diameter of the assembly, were it to need to fit in something like a bicycle wheel hub. 

Thought about it a bit too and what I said about the opposite point of contact was wrong too, no reason the opposing shaft wouldn't be on the same level, because they won't interfere.

Text is a poor drafting simulator...
